{
  "texts": [
    "Note that 10 documents only allow to reach as high as 0.91 of redacted metric.",
    "These results suggest that with good quality annotation, with double annotation and double pass to ensure quality, a few hundred documents are sufficient to train a system of sufficient quality at AP-HP's CDW.",
    "Note that the first annotation phase with three annotators lasted 6 days at a rate of 7 hours per day, and the second phase lasted approximately 42 person-hours, for a total of 168 person-hours for 3,600 documents.",
    "As the annotation of identifying information does not require special medical expertise, the human effort is not prohibitive.",
    "The system is not very sensitive to the omission of a document type in the training set, with most of the experiments Notes: Each result was averaged over five runs with different parameters random seed."
  ]
}